Description:
Responsibilities
Mathematical modelling of complex multi-body robotic systems, rigid/flexible robotic systems using the in-house developed simulator;
Use Python or other software languages to drive enhancements to robotic operations;
Identify automation opportunities to perform each robotic mission more simply than the last;
Translate operations into procedures, flight rules, and other real-time products for future robotics missions
Perform evaluation of robotics in-flight performance;
Tuning of the control system parameters of the manipulators to meet the performance and stability objectives required for the On-Orbit tasks;
Performing simulation runs to validate mathematical models, new parameters, and control algorithms;
Performing mission operations analysis using state-of-the-art simulation tools, computer vision algorithms, and AI/Machine Learning technologies;
Presenting analysis results to Technical Leads, Program management and customers;
Contributing to technology development (R&D activities) and to the Front End of the Business.
Basic Qualifications
A Bachelor’s or Master’s degree in Electrical, Systems, Computer, Aerospace Engineering or equivalent;
A minimum of 6 years of experience with focus on simulation and modelling;
The candidate should understand the product development cycle process, including analysis and design, development technologies and tools and technologies, version control, and testing methodologies;
Experience in simulating control systems design using MATLAB/Simulink;
Experience with a customer-facing position, handling design requirements, test acceptance, and verification is an asset;
Experience with Hardware-in-the-Loop & Software in the loop would be an asset;
Experience on control and dynamic modelling of multi-DOF manipulators is an asset;
Knowledge in thermodynamics, heat transfer and fluid dynamics would be an asset;
Ability to work in a team environment with project engineers, systems engineers, hardware engineers, and software engineers;
Excellent verbal and written communication skills.
Job Type: Full-time

